				<div class="tabContent">
		<div class="entry"><span class="date">April 26, 2016</span><h5><a href="//opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2016/04/26/guiding-a-first-generation-to-college/" title="Guiding a First Generation to College">Guiding a First Generation to College</a></h5><p><span class="excerpt-inner">Students who are new to America or lack college-educated parents often donât know their options.</span><a href="//opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2016/04/26/guiding-a-first-generation-to-college/" class="more-link">Read&nbsp;more&#8230;</a></p></div><div class="entry"><span class="date">April 19, 2016</span><h5><a href="//opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2016/04/19/how-dwindling-fish-stocks-got-a-reprieve/" title="How Dwindling Fish Stocks Got a Reprieve">How Dwindling Fish Stocks Got a Reprieve</a></h5><p><span class="excerpt-inner">Giving fishermen a business incentive to fish sustainably can âunleash their creative capacityâ to help solve the problem, says one expert. </span><a href="//opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2016/04/19/how-dwindling-fish-stocks-got-a-reprieve/" class="more-link">Read&nbsp;more&#8230;</a></p></div><div class="entry"><p class="more"><a href="//opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/category/fixes/">More From Fixes &raquo;</a></p></div>		</div>
				<div class="tabContent">
